Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Boil a large #pot{} of @salted water{for boiling} for the veg.

Peel and trim the @carrot{2}(peeled and trimmed) and @parsnip{2}(peeled and trimmed), then slice into 1cm thick rounds.

When boiling, add the carrot and parsnip to the water and simmer until fork tender, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve 100ml of cooking water, then drain in a #colander{} and set aside.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%units}(peeled).

Roughly chop the @hazelnuts{10%grams}, then pop into a #bowl{} with @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, half the @Italian Style Hard Cheese{2%units}(grated) and @oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then stir to combine.

Place a pan over medium heat with a drizzle of @?oil{for frying}.

Fry the garlic until fragrant, ~{30%secs}.

Mix in @creme fraiche{110%grams}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and @cooking water{100%ml}(reserved). Bring to the boil, then remove the pan from the heat. Stir in remaining cheese and season to taste with salt and pepper.

Pop the cooked parsnips and carrots into a small #oven dish{}.

Pour over the creamy sauce and sprinkle over the hazelnut breadcrumb mixture.

Bake in your oven until golden brown and bubbly, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Allow to rest for ~{10-20%minutes} before serving.